The <strong><code>assignedSlot</code></strong> property of the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/Text" title="The Text interface represents the textual content of Element or Attr.  If an element has no markup within its content, it has a single child implementing Text that contains the element's text.  However, if the element contains markup, it is parsed into information items and Text nodes that form its children."><code>Text</code></a> interface returns the <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLSlotElement" title="The HTMLSlotElement interface of the Shadow DOM API enables access to the name and assigned nodes of an HTML &lt;slot&gt; element."><code>HTMLSlotElement</code></a> object associated with the element.